</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1407,2008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
The putatively monophyletic 
<taxonomicName box="[493,610,1409,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritarsis">
<emphasis box="[493,610,1409,1432]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">nigritarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (Radenkoviċ 
<emphasis box="[851,912,1408,1432]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[922,979,1407,1431]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="2011.0">2011</number>
) includes the following 
<number box="[1267,1295,1407,1431]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="15.0">15</number>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Vujic et Radenkovic" authorityName="Vujic et Radenkovic" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. angustus</emphasis>
Vujiċ et Radenkoviċ
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[519,586,1445,1468]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sack" authorityName="Sack" box="[735,953,1444,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testaceus">
<emphasis box="[735,881,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. testaceus</emphasis>
Sack
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[980,1174,1444,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassifemoris">
<emphasis box="[980,1174,1444,1468]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. crassifemoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1195,1385,1444,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femoratoides">
<emphasis box="[1195,1385,1444,1468]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. femoratoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifemoris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. latifemoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[291,448,1481,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigritarsis">
<emphasis box="[291,448,1481,1504]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. nigritarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hurkmans, M." authorityName="Hurkmans, M." box="[468,803,1479,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidifrons">
<emphasis box="[468,626,1480,1504]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. nitidifrons</emphasis>
Hurkmans, 
<taxonomicName authority="Vujic et Radenkovic" authorityName="Vujic et Radenkovic" box="[772,803,1480,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadraticus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[772,803,1480,1504]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicName>
quadraticus Vujiċ et Radenkoviċ 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1197,1262,1480,1503]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifemoris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. latifemoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Hurkmans, M." authorityName="Hurkmans, M." box="[303,651,1516,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taniniensis">
<emphasis box="[303,468,1517,1540]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. taniniensis</emphasis>
Hurkmans, 
<taxonomicName box="[620,651,1517,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="testaceus">
<emphasis box="[620,651,1517,1540]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</taxonomicName>
testaceus and 
<taxonomicName box="[836,979,1517,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toscanus">
<emphasis box="[836,979,1517,1540]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. toscanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, plus species from the 
<taxonomicName box="[1273,1436,1516,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alagoezicus">
<emphasis box="[1273,1436,1516,1540]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M.alagoezicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex: 
<taxonomicName box="[269,446,1552,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alagoezicus">
<emphasis box="[269,446,1552,1576]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. alagoezicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, M. 
<taxonomicName authority="Vujic et Radenkovic" authorityName="Vujic et Radenkovic" box="[515,915,1551,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hakkariensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[515,656,1552,1576]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">hakkariensis</emphasis>
Vujiċ et Radenkoviċ
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[929,997,1552,1575]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(close to 
<taxonomicName box="[1129,1241,1552,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucasi">
<emphasis box="[1129,1241,1552,1576]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. lucasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[1272,1384,1552,1576]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucasi">
<emphasis box="[1272,1384,1552,1576]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. lucasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hurkmans" authorityName="Hurkmans" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satdagensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. satdagensis</emphasis>
Hurkmans
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hurkmans." authorityName="Hurkmans." box="[460,721,1588,1612]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schachti">
<emphasis box="[460,590,1588,1612]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">M. schachti</emphasis>
Hurkmans.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="445" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1407,2008]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,284]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="445" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1623,1648]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Relatively large (
<quantity box="[542,671,1623,1647]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="11.0">11–17 mm</quantity>
) species with white microtrichose longitudinal stripes on black mesoscutum and white microtrichose transverse bands on orange-brown (in females orange-black) tergites (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1602,1625]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,464,1566]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,421,1597]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Abdomen of M. angustus n. sp., dorsal view. A. male; B. female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219955/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
Figs. 
<number box="[151,167,1695,1719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<number box="[197,210,1695,1719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="5.0">5</number>
A, 
<number box="[245,259,1695,1719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="5.0">5</number>
B, 
<number box="[292,307,1695,1719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="4.0">4</number>
A); at least tergite 
<number box="[513,527,1695,1719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="2.0">2</number>
with reddish-orange marks. Mesoscutum covered with erect, yellow pile. Pile on metasternum erect, as long as those on hind coxa. Abdomen elongate, narrow and tapering, always longer than mesoscutum and scutellum together (
<figureCitation box="[572,651,1767,1791]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1602,1625]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,464,1566]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,421,1597]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Abdomen of M. angustus n. sp., dorsal view. A. male; B. female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219955/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
Figs. 
<number box="[637,651,1767,1791]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A–B, 
<number box="[719,732,1767,1791]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="5.0">5</number>
A–B). Posterior part of mid coxa without long pile. Tarsi dark brown/black dorsally and orange ventrally; at least metatarsus of hind legs always darkened dorsally (exceptionally, some specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[541,749,1840,1864]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[541,749,1840,1864]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Merodon angustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[755,814,1841,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can have completely yellow tarsi). First flagellomere at most twice as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[464,532,1876,1900]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,993,1016]" captionTargetBox="[165,1396,561,942]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,553,972]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Right antenna, inner view (basoflagellomere and pedicel); A-B. M. angustus n. sp.; C. M. hakkariensis n. sp.; D. M. quadraticus n. sp. A, C, D males; B female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219956/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
Fig. 
<number box="[516,532,1876,1900]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs without spikes or other protuberances (
<figureCitation box="[1047,1155,1876,1900]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 7" captionStart-1="FIGURE 8" captionStart-2="FIGURE 9" captionStartId-0="6.[151,250,1598,1621]" captionStartId-1="7.[151,250,1572,1595]" captionStartId-2="8.[151,250,1359,1382]" captionTargetBox-0="[172,1416,1099,1562]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1428,438,1527]" captionTargetBox-2="[282,1306,315,1325]" captionTargetId-0="figure@6.[158,1429,1075,1576]" captionTargetId-1="figure@7.[151,1436,409,1551]" captionTargetId-2="figure@8.[266,1321,303,1337]" captionTargetPageId-0="6" captionTargetPageId-1="7" captionTargetPageId-2="8" captionText-0="FIGURE 7. Left hind femur and tibia of males lateral view; A. M. hakkariensis n. sp.; B. M. lucasi; C. M. alagoezicus. xlamella." captionText-1="FIGURE 8. Left hind femur and tibia, lateral view; A-B. M. angustus n. sp.; C-D. M. testaceus; A, C—males; B, D—females." captionText-2="FIGURE 9. Left hind femur and tibia of males, lateral view; A. M. quadraticus n. sp.; B. M. femoratoides; C. M. nitidifrons." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/219957/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/219958/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/219959/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
Figs. 
<number box="[1110,1155,1876,1900]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="8.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.0">7–9</number>
</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia: anterior lobe of surstylus (
<figureCitation box="[365,451,1911,1935]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1422,1445]" captionTargetBox="[175,1410,673,1389]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,661,1401]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 10. Male genitalia, epandrium, lateral view. A. M. angustus n. sp.; B. M. testaceus; a—anterior lobe of the surstylus, p—posterior lobe of the surstylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219960/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
Fig. 
<number box="[422,451,1911,1935]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
A: a) more or less of rhomboid shape, covered with dense short pile, except in the 
<taxonomicName box="[151,283,1948,1972]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alagoezicus">
<emphasis box="[151,283,1948,1972]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">alagoezicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex of species where the anterior lobe of the surstylus is transformed into a narrow, elongate, strongly curved projection (
<figureCitation box="[461,530,1984,2008]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1192,1215]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,473,1167]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,473,1167]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Distribution of M. angustus n. sp. () and M. testaceus ()." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219952/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
Fig. 
<number box="[514,530,1984,2008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
: a); posterior lobe of the surstylus (
<figureCitation box="[927,1008,1984,2008]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1422,1445]" captionTargetBox="[175,1410,673,1389]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,661,1401]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 10. Male genitalia, epandrium, lateral view. A. M. angustus n. sp.; B. M. testaceus; a—anterior lobe of the surstylus, p—posterior lobe of the surstylus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219960/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
Fig. 
<number box="[979,1008,1984,2008]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
A: p) usually longer than anterior one; interior accessory lobe of posterior lobe of surstylus narrow and long (in lateral view, 
<figureCitation box="[1200,1286,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1089,1112]" captionTargetBox="[336,1254,453,1059]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[313,1273,445,1069]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 12. Male genitalia, epandrium, lateral view. A. M. quadraticus n. sp.; B. M. femoratoides; a—anterior lobe of the surstylus, p—posterior lobe of the surstylus, i—interior accessory lobe of posterior lobe of the surstylus; c—cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219962/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">
Fig. 
<number box="[1257,1286,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="445" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
A: i); cercus rectangular, without prominences (
<figureCitation box="[538,619,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1089,1112]" captionTargetBox="[336,1254,453,1059]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[313,1273,445,1069]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 12. Male genitalia, epandrium, lateral view. A. M. quadraticus n. sp.; B. M. femoratoides; a—anterior lobe of the surstylus, p—posterior lobe of the surstylus, i—interior accessory lobe of posterior lobe of the surstylus; c—cercus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/219962/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="445">
Fig. 
<number box="[590,619,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="445" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
A: c). Hypandrium narrow, elongate and sickle–shaped (
